For each bouton, SVs were uniformly distributed inside the SV cluster. For this, the modeling tool MCell was used.
These files are needed to run the model. The files named Scene_geometry_xx.py contain information about the objects in the the Blender scene (xx here refers to the series name).
Once run, the location of the SVs is saved in the folder xx_seed_#. To run the model with a specific set the geometry for that set should be used (so change the set).
The position of the SVs is then read with read_ves_pos.py and SVs are added in those positions.

